<head>FISH</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">魚</item>
        <item xml:lang="och">魚</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>COLD-BLOODES AQUATIC ANIMAL which HAS a SPINE.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The common general term for a fish is yú 魚.</p>
<p>2. Lín 鱗 can be also used as a general term for a fish, because the body of a fish is covered with scales (lín 鱗 ).</p>
<p>3. Xiān 鮮 is a fairly rare general term for a fish.</p>
<p>4. Jīng 鯨 (traditional reading qíng) refers to a whale. See FISHES</p>
<p>5. Shā 鯊 refers to a shark.</p>
<p>6. Guān 鰥 is the kind of a very large fish living in rivers and lakes. It has a long and narrow mouth and moves alone.</p>
        </div>
<div type="huang-jingui">
<p>HUANG JINGUI 2006</p>
<p>ANIMALS 24.</p>
<p>魚，魚類總稱。</p>
<p>其別稱，較早者 “ 水蟲 ” 。</p>
<p>常見者 “ 鮮 ” 。</p>
<p>從魚的外部特徵則可通稱為 “ 鱗 ” 。</p>
<p>ANIMALS 25. 鱘，古代主要指白鱘科的白鱘，世界上最大的淡水魚。鱘魚又稱淫魚。</p>
<p>鱣，鱘科大魚的古名。鰉（ ?? 、黃魚），中古起鱣的別名，亦稱鱘鰉。</p>
<p>鮪，廣義泛指白鱘和大小鱘魚，狹義指達氏鱘。鮥指小鮪。</p>
        </div>
